  <title>Add/Edit Course Types</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Add/Edit Course Types</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">A <text style="font-weight:bold;">Course Type</text> categorizes Courses &amp; Activities into groups. Common Course Types might include...</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="margin-bottom:0px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-bottom:0px;">Art</li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-bottom:0px;">Exercise</li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-bottom:0px;">Games</li>
      <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-bottom:0px;">Social</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-bottom:0px;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Each course type record also contains a <text style="font-weight:bold;">Short Name </text>field. A short name has a maximum of 15 characters. The short name is used on system graphics where screen space is at a premium.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Once created, a Course Type may not be deleted. If a Course Type is no longer required, tick the <text style="font-style:italic;">Discontinued</text> check box.</para>
  </body>
